Combos rather nicely with [Greed](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Greed), but I suppose that's beside the point.  

Throw in [Words of Worship](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Words of Worship) and we'll restart the conversation.  

Exile a card: Add ![Black](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=B&type=symbol)![Black](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=B&type=symbol).  
![Black](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=B&type=symbol): Draw a card and lose 2 life.  
![1](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=1&type=symbol)![Black](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=B&type=symbol): Gain 3 life.  

To cut a long story short, this combination allows you to turn any card in your hand into:  
1) A ![Black or Green](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=BG&type=symbol) [Rite of Flame](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Rite of Flame) that can only be cast for ![0](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=0&type=symbol) (instead of its normal ![Red](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=R&type=symbol));  
2) An [Inspiration](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Inspiration) that can only be cast for 4 life (instead of its normal ![3](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=3&type=symbol)![Blue](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=U&type=symbol));  
3) A [Catalog](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Catalog) that can only be cast for 1 life (instead of its normal ![2](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=2&type=symbol)![Blue](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=U&type=symbol));  
4) A [Healing Salve](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Healing Salve) (*roughly*) that can only be cast for ![0](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=0&type=symbol) (instead of its normal ![White](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=W&type=symbol));  
in addition to giving you access to a permanent [Channel](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Channel) at double the life-cost, as well as the abilities of each enchantment on its own.  

